	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64284936"><p>OneDrive is ON BY DEFAULT!  I have friends who lost files this way, not realizing that files were copied off of the PC, put into the Cloud, then DELETED from the local drive, then the gawdawful UI means that trying to fix this can make some files lost.  One Drive treats your local drive like a most-recently-used cache and not as storage.  Thank heavens for secure local backups uninfected by any Microsoft code.</p><p>Step one after upgrading to W11 is to disable OneDrive if you were required to create a Microsoft Account.  Step two after upgrading, delete your Microsoft Account ASAP.  Step three, go about limiting the built-in spyware.  Yes, disable OneDrive _before_ the spyware.</p></div>
